right move. Since we can't modify the repo, maybe I could try a temporary Gradle command to test this efficiently?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying log4j dependencies**\\n\\nI need to mention that the resolved artifact states log4j-core is optional, but its 2.18 version for Log4j1Configuration and PropertySetter directly references core classes. The documentation specifies that we need log4j-api, log4j-core, and log4j-1.2-api for the converter. It's important to align versions, so coordinating with \\\"org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-core:2.18.0\\\" makes sense. Also, another optional dependency to consider is `javax.jms:javax.jms-api` for the JMSAppender.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"log4j-1.2-api 2.18.0 has core-dependent compatibility paths: the artifact declares log4j-core as optional, but normal Log4j 1.x migration/use requires a Log4j 2 backend and 2.18.0 classes such as Log4j1Configuration are referenced from PropertySetter/configuration code.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-core:2.18.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The compatibility bridge delegates meaningful Log4j 1.x logging/configuration behavior to Log4j 2 Core; in 2.18.0 PropertySetter references Log4j1Configuration.DEFAULT_LEVEL, whose class depends on log4j-core classes, so tests without core can silently fail conversion paths instead of covering normal bridge behavior.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image or environment variable is needed. Tests that set Log4j-related system properties should restore them after each test and should avoid relying on ambient logging configuration.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"log4j-core is optional in the published POM, so adding it intentionally broadens the test classpath to the normal runtime/backend setup rather than the minimal API-only setup.\",\n    \"If tests cover optional integrations such as JMS appenders, further optional APIs may be needed, but they are not required for baseline meaningful coverage.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_08f9236a8821eec6016a3e8339ca5881908679c1270f3737db\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 907, "output": 852, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32991, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782481710481, "responseId": "resp_08f9236a8821eec6016a3e832f06e08190af0ebb12eccadc02"}, "toolResults": []}
